# Reverse-Spec UI

When the user is asking for UI, visual communication, design direction, finished HTML, or reacting to references/screenshots, start from the finished artifact and work backward.

Use this sequence:
- finished artifact or reference
- composition choices
- user selection/cropping/annotation
- reverse-spec notes
- components and implementation

Rules:
- Show visual options before long explanations
- Prefer image/caption boards, composition galleries, crops, and annotated references
- Text is secondary; use it to extract meaning from selected visuals
- Do not begin with Mermaid, same-sized labeled boxes, or utilitarian wireframes unless explicitly requested
- Background dictates foreground; preserve figure/ground, scale, depth, and center of gravity when translating into UI

If a visual artifact does not exist yet, gather strong public references first and build from those.
